like a cut cat
Homonym Number:
Word Class:phrase
Sense Number:
Definition:emphasising a speedy (or vigorous) action, an apter and more usual rendering of 'like a scalded cat/a cat on hot bricks'.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: ca1938 Havelock.
